                  <h5> <a name="gov"></a>Government </h5>
                  <p>Hawaii is a state of the United States of America. A popularly 
                    elected Governor and Lieutenant Governor administer Hawaii. 
                    They are both in power for a four-year term. The local parliament 
                    comprises a House of Representatives of 51 members, elected 
                    every two years, and a Senate of 25 members, elected for terms 
                    of four years. The legislature meets annually in the capital, 
                    Honolulu. Hawaii sends two representatives and two senators 
                    to the Congress in Washington. 
                  <h5><b><a name="res"></a></b>Resources </h5>
                  <p>Tourism is the main source of revenue, with visitors bringing 
										in more than $A18 billion. More than 6.9 million tourists 
										visited Hawaii in 2000, the majority from mainland USA and 
										Japan. Most hotels in the state are Japanese-owned. The tourism 
										industry provides employment for an estimated 250,000 people.
									<p>US Federal defence spending ($A8.1 billion) is the other 
										major earner. The US Pacific Command, based in Hawaii, is 
										the largest of the American military. 
									<p>Agriculture, once the main source of revenue, is still a 
                    significant contributor, in particular the production of sugar, 
                    pineapple, flowers and macadamia nuts.<br>
                    <br>
                  <h5><a name="hist"></a>History </h5>
                  <p>The islands of Hawaii are believed to have been settled around 600 years AD, by Polynesian navigators who originated from the Marquesas Islands. A second migration from Tahiti seems to have occurred years later. 

<p>Captain James Cook, the first European to come across the islands in 1778, named them Sandwich Islands in honour of his patron, the Earl of Sandwich. One year later, on the way back from his journey to the northwest coast of America, Cook was killed on the island of Hawaii. 

<p>From the end of the 18th century to the end of the 19th, the Hawaiian islands were united under the dynasty of the Kamehameha, a chiefly family from the island of Hawaii. 

<p>With the arrival of Europeans, the native population, which was estimated at
300,000 in Cook's time, dropped to 40,000 by 1890. 

<p>Following the collapse of the whaling industry in the 1860s, sugar became the new basis for Hawaii's economy. Thousands of Chinese, Japanese and Pacific labourers were imported during this period. 

<p>After years of political instability, Hawaii was finally annexed by the United States in August 1898 and formally became a Territory in June 1900. 

<p>Following the attack on the naval base of Pearl Harbour by the Japanese in December 1941, the island of Oahu became the strategic centre for the war operations in Asia and the Pacific. 

<p>Hawaii became the 50th state of the USA on August 21 1959.


                  <p><br>
                  <h5>Main Issues </h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li> 
                      <p>land rights for native Hawaiians</p>
